The Makefile and patches automatically set up the JPMail demo from 2006.
Has been tested under openjdk 1.6 and 1.7

First:
  Set the environment variable JAVA_HOME to the root of your jdk install
  Eg:
    export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-6-openjdk-i386

Run:
  make download - to download jif 2.0.1 and jpmail (latest/last)
  make          - to patch and build jpmail
  make clean    - to remove the extracted and compiled jif and jpmail
